text: Masjid Al-Mamoor, also known as the Jamaica Muslim Center, is one of the largest multi-purpose Muslim establishments in Jamaica, New York. The center includes a mosque, a school, and a place for religious gathering and eating facilities. Masjid Al-Mamoor was started by mostly Bangladeshi-Americans, as it is located in the heavily Bangladeshi-American locality of Jamaica, New York. ==External links== * Category:Asian-American culture in New York City Category:Bangladeshi-American culture Category:Mosques in New York City Category:Non-profit organizations based in New York City Category:Religious buildings and structures in Queens, New York Category:Jamaica, Queens
